  "root_text": {
    "an4.65:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4.65 ",
    "an4.65:0.2": "7. Pattakammavagga ",
    "an4.65:0.3": "Rūpasutta ",
    "an4.65:1.1": "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṁvijjamānā lokasmiṁ. ",
    "an4.65:1.2": "Katame cattāro? ",
    "an4.65:1.3": "Rūpappamāṇo rūpappasanno, ghosappamāṇo ghosappasanno, lūkhappamāṇo lūkhappasanno, dhammappamāṇo dhammappasanno—",
    "an4.65:1.4": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṁvijjamānā lokasminti. ",
    "an4.65:2.1": "Ye ca rūpe pamāṇiṁsu, ",
    "an4.65:2.2": "ye ca ghosena anvagū; ",
    "an4.65:2.3": "Chandarāgavasūpetā, ",
    "an4.65:2.4": "nābhijānanti te janā. ",
    "an4.65:3.1": "Ajjhattañca na jānāti, ",
    "an4.65:3.2": "bahiddhā ca na passati; ",
    "an4.65:3.3": "Samantāvaraṇo bālo, ",
    "an4.65:3.4": "sa ve ghosena vuyhati. ",
    "an4.65:4.1": "Ajjhattañca na jānāti, ",
    "an4.65:4.2": "bahiddhā ca vipassati; ",
    "an4.65:4.3": "Bahiddhā phaladassāvī, ",
    "an4.65:4.4": "sopi ghosena vuyhati. ",
    "an4.65:5.1": "Ajjhattañca pajānāti, ",
    "an4.65:5.2": "bahiddhā ca vipassati; ",
    "an4.65:5.3": "Vinīvaraṇadassāvī, ",
    "an4.65:5.4": "na so ghosena vuyhatī”ti. ",
    "an4.65:5.5": "Pañcamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an4.65:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 4.65 ",
    "an4.65:0.2": "7. Fitting Deeds ",
    "an4.65:0.3": "Appearance ",
    "an4.65:1.1": "“Mendicants, these four individuals are found in the world. ",
    "an4.65:1.2": "What four? ",
    "an4.65:1.3": "There are those whose estimation of and confidence in others is based on their appearance, on their voice, on their mortification, and on principle. ",
    "an4.65:1.4": "These are the four individuals found in the world. ",
    "an4.65:2.1": "Those who judge on appearance, ",
    "an4.65:2.2": "and those swayed by a voice, ",
    "an4.65:2.3": "are full of desire and greed; ",
    "an4.65:2.4": "those people just don’t understand. ",
    "an4.65:3.1": "Not knowing what’s inside, ",
    "an4.65:3.2": "nor seeing what’s outside, ",
    "an4.65:3.3": "the fool shut in on every side, ",
    "an4.65:3.4": "gets carried away by a voice. ",
    "an4.65:4.1": "Not knowing what’s inside, ",
    "an4.65:4.2": "but discerning what’s outside, ",
    "an4.65:4.3": "seeing the fruit outside, ",
    "an4.65:4.4": "they’re also carried away by a voice. ",
    "an4.65:5.1": "Understanding what’s inside, ",
    "an4.65:5.2": "and discerning what’s outside, ",
    "an4.65:5.3": "seeing without hindrances, ",
    "an4.65:5.4": "they don’t get carried away by a voice.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an4.65:0.3": "Rūpasutta → rūpa (ppamāṇa) suttaṁ (bj) ",
    "an4.65:2.1": "ca rūpe pamāṇiṁsu → ye ca rūpena pāmiṁsu (bj, sya-all, km, pts1ed) ",
    "an4.65:2.4": "nābhijānanti te janā → na te jānanti taṁ janaṁ (bj, pts1ed); na te jānanti tañjanaṁ (sya-all, km) "
  },
